WEBVTT

00:04.371 --> 00:05.339 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.372 --> 00:06.573 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.607 --> 00:10.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: from
torture to
banning Muslims.

00:10.077 --> 00:15.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At his confirmation hearing to
be the next
attorney general, Senator Jeff
Sessions lays

00:15.682 --> 00:20.053 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
out legal limits to
president-elect Trump's
campaign statements.

00:20.087 --> 00:26.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, our series The Obama Years
continues
with a look at the president's
legacy on criminal

00:26.059 --> 00:27.794 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
justice.

00:27.828 --> 00:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And how integrating arts in the
classroom
helps turn around poorly
performing schools.

00:33.433 --> 00:39.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALFRE WOODARD, Actress: Art
completes not
only the education, but it
completes the human

00:39.439 --> 00:43.677 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
being, our ability to create,
and to express
that creation.

00:43.710 --> 00:47.514 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:47.547 --> 00:51.752 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:51.785 --> 01:03.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It's opening day
of confirmation
season for team Trump.

01:03.797 --> 01:08.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Senator Jeff Sessions, the
nominee for
attorney general, was leadoff
man.

01:08.702 --> 01:13.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He went before colleagues on the
Senate Judiciary
Committee, defending his views
on race and

01:13.640 --> 01:18.745 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
civil rights and, at times,
separating himself
from the man who chose him.

01:18.779 --> 01:20.847 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins begins our
coverage.

01:20.881 --> 01:27.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Alabama Senator
Jeff Sessions
walked into his hearing to some
as a longtime,

01:27.454 --> 01:34.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
accomplished senator unfairly
accused of prejudice,
to others, as an extreme
conservative who

01:34.728 --> 01:36.730 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
stokes racial divide.

01:36.763 --> 01:41.435 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In his opening remarks, the
attorney general
hopeful laid out his theme to
both sides,

01:41.468 --> 01:43.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
saying he would put the law
above his own
views.

01:43.904 --> 01:45.405 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:45.439 --> 01:46.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS (R-AL), Attorney
General Nominee:
I have always loved the law.

01:46.506 --> 01:50.410 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is the very foundation of our
great country.

01:50.444 --> 01:52.980 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's the exceptional foundation
of America.

01:53.013 --> 01:58.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Sessions'
politics and
view of the law have sparked
furious opposition.

01:58.385 --> 02:04.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 1986, accusations of racially
insensitive
remarks and actions led the
Senate to reject

02:04.658 --> 02:05.926 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
him for a federal judgeship.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.761 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:07.794 --> 02:09.896 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DIANNE FEINSTEIN (D),
California: And the
committee has received letters
of opposition

02:09.930 --> 02:16.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from 400 different civil rights
organizations,
1,400 law professors.

02:16.370 --> 02:22.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Today, ranking
Democrat California's
Dianne Feinstein opened by
pointing to fears

02:22.109 --> 02:26.079 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that Sessions wouldn't enforce
laws fairly
to all.

02:26.113 --> 02:28.248 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Sessions insisted the
accusations were all
false.

02:28.281 --> 02:29.549 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:29.583 --> 02:35.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: This caricature
of me in 1986
was not correct.

02:35.088 --> 02:37.557 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have become United States
attorney.

02:37.591 --> 02:44.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I supported, as the civil rights
attorney
said, major civil rights cases
in my districts.

02:44.831 --> 02:54.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The hearing was
interrupted
regularly by protesters raising
an array of

02:54.341 --> 02:58.478 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
concerns, from civil rights to
immigration
to marijuana policy.

02:58.512 --> 03:03.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Committee Democrats like largely
withheld
fire today, instead focusing on
questions

03:03.483 --> 03:05.018 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about major issues like
abortion.

03:05.052 --> 03:06.753 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:06.787 --> 03:10.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANNE FEINSTEIN: You have
referred to Roe
vs. Wade as -- quote -- "one of
the worst,

03:10.390 --> 03:16.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
colossally erroneous Supreme
Court decisions
of all time" -- end quote.

03:16.396 --> 03:17.964 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Is that still your view?

03:17.998 --> 03:18.965 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:18.999 --> 03:19.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFF SESSIONS: It is.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.301 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is law of the land.

03:21.334 --> 03:25.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has been so established and
settled for
quite a long time.

03:25.138 --> 03:28.608 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it deserves respect, and I
would respect
it and follow it.

03:28.642 --> 03:34.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This was
Sessions' refrain:
His view hasn't changed; his job
would.

03:34.047 --> 03:35.916 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Similarly, on same-sex marriage.

03:35.949 --> 03:37.784 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:37.818 --> 03:41.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: The five justices
on the Supreme
Court, a majority of the court,
has established

03:41.288 --> 03:45.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the definition of marriage for
the entire
United States of America.

03:45.659 --> 03:47.427 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I will follow that decision.

03:47.461 --> 03:48.595 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: And on
water-boarding.

03:48.628 --> 03:50.363 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:50.397 --> 03:53.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: Congress has
taken an action
now that makes it absolutely
improper and

03:53.867 --> 04:02.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
illegal to use water-boarding or
any form
of torture in the United States
by our military

04:02.042 --> 04:04.945 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and by all other departments and
agencies.

04:04.978 --> 04:09.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It was on
immigration, an
issue where Sessions will have
tremendous

04:09.316 --> 04:11.084 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
power, that he took a staunch
stand.

04:11.118 --> 04:13.086 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:13.120 --> 04:19.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: I do believe that
if you continually
go through a cycle of amnesty,
that you undermine

04:19.126 --> 04:25.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the respect for the law and
encourage more
illegal immigration into
America.

04:25.499 --> 04:28.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I believe the American people
spoke clearly
in this election.

04:28.735 --> 04:31.238 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I believe they agreed with my
basic view.

04:31.271 --> 04:35.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: One question
was asked by
both parties: How would Sessions
handle any

04:35.408 --> 04:39.212 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cases involving president-elect
Trump and
his family?

04:39.246 --> 04:42.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sessions insisted he would
resign, rather
than do something unlawful.

04:42.682 --> 04:46.019 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Later, Democratic Senator
Sheldon Whitehouse
asked about Russia.

04:46.052 --> 04:47.854 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:47.888 --> 04:49.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHELDON WHITEHOUSE (D), Rhode
Island: Will
the Department of Justice and
the FBI under

04:49.756 --> 04:56.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
your administration be allowed
to continue
to investigate the Russian
connection, even

04:56.730 --> 05:01.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
if it leads to the Trump camp
and Trump interests
and associates?

05:01.635 --> 05:05.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Sessions didn't
answer directly,
and brought up another country.

05:05.872 --> 05:07.507 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:07.541 --> 05:12.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: If there are laws
violated
and they can be prosecuted, then
of course

05:12.379 --> 05:15.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you will have to handle that in
an appropriate
way.

05:15.348 --> 05:23.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would say that the problem may
turn out
to be, as in the Chinese hacking
of hundreds

05:23.990 --> 05:29.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of thousands of maybe millions,
of records,
it has to be handled at a
political level.

05:29.930 --> 05:33.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Sessions told
the committee
he would recuse himself on cases
involving

05:33.633 --> 05:37.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hillary Clinton's e-mail, but
asked if he'd
recuse himself from any Trump
investigations?

05:38.004 --> 05:39.706 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:39.739 --> 05:44.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: I would review it
and try to
do the right thing as to whether
or not it

05:44.077 --> 05:48.949 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
should stay within the
jurisdiction of the
attorney general or not.

05:48.982 --> 05:52.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And we may see
more drama
and strong words tomorrow.

05:52.419 --> 05:56.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's when there will be
witnesses for and
against Mr. Sessions.

05:56.156 --> 06:00.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa, thanks,
along with other
nominee confirmations.

06:00.660 --> 06:06.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, Lisa, separately today, the
president-elect
told The New York Times in an
interview that

06:06.066 --> 06:12.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he wants Republicans in Congress
to replace
Obamacare, the Affordable Care
Act, at the

06:12.472 --> 06:16.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
same time or very shortly after
they repeal
it.

06:16.476 --> 06:20.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How does that square with what
Republicans
are thinking and planning to do?

06:20.313 --> 06:23.283 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's
certainly been the
other big headline on Capitol
Hill today.

06:23.316 --> 06:27.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is at odds with the direction
Republicans
had been going in.

06:27.354 --> 06:31.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Right now, the repeal itself
seems likely
to happen some time perhaps by
the end of

06:31.391 --> 06:36.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
January, at its fastest, and
replacement,
Republicans haven't agreed on a
timeline for

06:36.129 --> 06:38.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that, some of them looking at
even maybe this
summer.

06:38.965 --> 06:43.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But now we have had word from
the House Republican
Speaker Paul Ryan today, saying
he hopes to

06:43.503 --> 06:48.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
add in some concurrent elements
of the replace
as they repeal.

06:48.908 --> 06:53.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, all in all, Judy, this
is sort of
the longtime Republican leaders
in Congress

06:53.246 --> 06:59.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
coming, perhaps clashing with to
some degree
the new Republican president to
be.

06:59.686 --> 07:03.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, just quickly,
Lisa, this
could mean a delay in the repeal
vote?

07:03.390 --> 07:06.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: No, I don't
think so, but
I think what it means, it will
be very difficult

07:06.860 --> 07:10.030 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to meet Donald Trump's timeline
of an immediate
repeal.

07:10.063 --> 07:12.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The repeal itself is probably
still weeks
away.

07:12.465 --> 07:16.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa Desjardins
at the Capitol,
thank you.

07:16.936 --> 07:22.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: A
federal jury sentenced
Dylann Roof to death for killing
nine black

07:22.242 --> 07:25.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
worshipers at a church in
Charleston, South
Carolina.

07:25.745 --> 07:31.251 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The white supremacist
represented himself,
but he presented no case and
didn't ask the

07:31.284 --> 07:33.119 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
jury to spare his life.

07:33.153 --> 07:37.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Afterward, one man whose sister
was killed
called the verdict a hollow
victory.

07:38.024 --> 07:41.995 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MELVIN GRAHAM, Brother of
Victim: My sister
is still gone.

07:42.028 --> 07:49.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I wish that this verdict could
have brought
her back, but it can't.

07:49.369 --> 07:58.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what it can do is just send
a message
to those who feel the way he
feels that this

07:58.678 --> 08:01.081 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
community will not tolerate it.

08:01.114 --> 08:05.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Roof is the first
person sentenced
to die for a federal hate crime.

08:06.019 --> 08:09.789 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He still faces murder charges in
state court.

08:09.823 --> 08:14.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama is back home
tonight in Chicago
for his farewell address to the
nation.

08:14.661 --> 08:19.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is expected to reflect on his
eight years
in office before an audience of
thousands

08:19.766 --> 08:21.568 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of supporters.

08:21.601 --> 08:25.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a Facebook post today, he
previewed his
message, saying -- quote -- "We
have reaffirmed

08:25.805 --> 08:30.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the belief that we can make a
difference with
our own hands, in our own time."

08:30.810 --> 08:35.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PBS will have special live
coverage of the
president's speech later
tonight.

08:35.915 --> 08:41.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The man in line to be the next
secretary of
homeland security says building
barriers along

08:41.154 --> 08:43.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Mexican border is not
enough.

08:44.023 --> 08:48.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Retired Marine General John F.
Kelly had his
Senate confirmation hearing
today.

08:48.762 --> 08:54.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Among the questions: What about
president-elect
Trump's promise to build a
border wall?

08:54.334 --> 08:56.169 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

08:56.202 --> 08:57.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KELLY (RET.), Homeland
Security Secretary
Nominee: Certainly, as a
military person that

08:57.971 --> 09:02.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
understands defense and
defenses, a physical
barrier, in and of itself, will
not do the

09:02.575 --> 09:03.543 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
job.

09:03.576 --> 09:05.612 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It has to be, really, a layered
defense.

09:05.645 --> 09:09.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you were to build a wall from
the Pacific
to the Gulf of Mexico, you would
still have

09:09.749 --> 09:15.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to back that wall up with
patrolling by human
beings, by sensors, by
observation devices.

09:15.355 --> 09:20.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Kelly also said
he doesn't
support the idea of a registry
for Muslims

09:20.527 --> 09:23.062 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
or for other religious groups.

09:23.096 --> 09:28.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Afghanistan, nearly 40 people
died today
in a pair of bombings that
rocked Kabul.

09:28.067 --> 09:30.303 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Taliban claimed
responsibility.

09:30.336 --> 09:35.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The blasts erupted near the
Afghan parliament
complex during evening rush
hour.

09:35.241 --> 09:39.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In addition to the dead, more
than 70 others
were wounded.

09:39.913 --> 09:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Thousands of people in Northern
California
remain under evacuation orders
tonight, as

09:44.451 --> 09:47.821 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
heavy rain and snow roll over
the region.

09:47.854 --> 09:52.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even police vehicles got stuck
in the Sierra
Nevada Mountains, where up to 10
feet of snow

09:52.959 --> 09:57.063 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was falling, and even ski
resorts had to shut
down.

09:57.096 --> 10:02.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Elsewhere, flooding in Sonoma
County is now
the worst in a decade, forcing
officials to

10:02.435 --> 10:06.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
open a Sacramento dam for the
first time since
2005.

10:06.840 --> 10:09.876 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Wall Street mostly marked time
today.

10:09.909 --> 10:15.114 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
lost nearly
32 points to close at 19855.

10:15.148 --> 10:17.584 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 20 points, and
the S&amp;P 500
was unchanged.

10:17.617 --> 10:18.585 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the newly crowned champions
of college
football are back home in
Clemson, South Carolina,

10:18.618 --> 10:20.253 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
tonight, after an epic victory
over Alabama.

10:20.286 --> 10:21.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Tigers scored last night
with one second
left on the clock to win 35 to
31.

10:21.621 --> 10:23.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was a rematch of last year's
