my successor
at some point in the near term.

14:56.329 --> 14:58.364 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You haven't met
with him yet?

14:58.397 --> 15:00.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: No, I haven't met
with him yet.

15:00.733 --> 15:02.001 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Do you expect to?

15:02.034 --> 15:03.936 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN KERRY: I do.

15:03.970 --> 15:08.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What are the one
or two things
that you wish you had known in
the very beginning

15:08.808 --> 15:11.477 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that you only learned later and
maybe painfully?

15:11.511 --> 15:22.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: What troubles me a
little bit
is that people are not
separating a remarkable

15:22.255 --> 15:34.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
transformation that is taking
place globally
naturally from things that we're
really responsible

15:34.734 --> 15:35.668 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for.

15:35.701 --> 15:38.871 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Let me give you an example, Arab
Spring.

15:38.905 --> 15:40.673 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We didn't start the Arab Spring.

15:40.706 --> 15:43.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We couldn't have stopped the
Arab Spring,
particularly with respect to
Syria.

15:43.776 --> 15:47.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think there are some
things that might
have been able to have been
done.

15:47.847 --> 15:50.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But that had nothing to do with
the red line.

15:50.716 --> 15:54.787 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And let's make that absolutely
clear, folks.

15:54.821 --> 15:58.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Obama never retreated
from his red
line.

15:58.691 --> 16:05.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He never changed his mind about
his readiness
to bomb Assad to make it clear,
you don't

16:05.531 --> 16:08.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
use chemical weapons, never.

16:08.501 --> 16:11.304 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a mythology that's grown
up around
this.

16:11.337 --> 16:19.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the greatest challenges
we all face
right now, not just America, but
every country

16:19.045 --> 16:29.789 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the world, is, we are living
in a factless
political environment.

16:29.822 --> 16:38.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And every country in the world
better stop
and start worrying about
authoritarian populism

16:38.130 --> 16:45.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the absence of substance in
our dialogue,
if you call it that.

16:45.538 --> 16:47.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What can the U.S.
do about
that?

16:47.506 --> 16:49.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: Well, we're going to
have to fight
for it.

16:49.709 --> 16:54.213 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think a lot of people are
struggling with
the, what do you do about it?

16:54.247 --> 17:04.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If policy is going to be made in
140 characters
on Twitter, and every reasonable
measurement

17:04.090 --> 17:10.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of accountability is being
bypassed, and people
don't care about it, we have a
problem.

17:10.696 --> 17:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's not just our problem
here in the
United States.

17:14.433 --> 17:16.168 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's all over the world.

17:16.202 --> 17:20.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Secretary Kerry
also called
for a new Marshall Plan to help
countries

17:20.806 --> 17:26.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in critical regions around the
world educate
their exploding youth
populations and prevent

17:26.712 --> 17:40.293 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
them from being radicalized.

17:40.326 --> 17:45.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Sunday, one of the founders
of the Islamic
Revolution in Iran died at age
82.

17:45.798 --> 17:53.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ali Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani
helped to lead
the 1979 uprising, and went on
to serve both

17:53.139 --> 17:58.477 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
