think we may

40:23.321 --> 40:27.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not feel that he's really
leveling with us
in the way that other presidents
have.

40:27.392 --> 40:31.062 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Annette
Gordon-Reed, the White
House did release just a small
portion of

40:31.095 --> 40:34.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what the president is going to
say.

40:34.999 --> 40:39.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's basically he's saying -- he
talks about
the beauty of democracy and the
experiment

40:39.437 --> 40:41.239 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
itself, government.

40:41.272 --> 40:44.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said, "This is a great gift
our founders
gave us, the freedom to chase
our individual

40:44.642 --> 40:47.779 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
dreams through our sweat, toil
and imagination."

40:47.812 --> 40:52.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But is Michael right, he's going
to need to
say more than that about what
he's got in

40:52.517 --> 40:55.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mind for the future, or else
people may be
disappointed?

40:55.653 --> 41:00.692 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANNETTE GORDON-REED: Well, I
think we're in
unchartered waters here.

41:00.725 --> 41:03.728 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have a president who has
never held office
before.

41:03.761 --> 41:07.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is one of the things that
was apparently
one of his attractions to
people.

41:07.498 --> 41:10.034 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We don't know what to expect.

41:10.068 --> 41:11.836 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so I think Michael is right.

41:11.869 --> 41:17.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We really do expect to have him
say something
that indicates what kind of role
he's going

41:17.208 --> 41:23.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to play after he leaves office,
because we're
in an unprecedented era, and the
president

41:23.548 --> 41:25.450 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
has to be different perhaps.

41:25.483 --> 41:29.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The post-presidency has to be
different, not
just matter of a person getting
their library

41:29.487 --> 41:31.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
together or whatever.

41:31.189 --> 41:34.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When he's talking about the
experiment, the
American experiment, the
question is, how

41:34.959 --> 41:38.596 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
does it continue in this
particular moment?

41:38.629 --> 41:41.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I expect he will say
something like
that.

41:41.332 --> 41:45.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Michael, is there
-- I mean,
looking at what presidents have
done through

41:45.737 --> 41:53.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
history, post-presidency, have
their actions
been affected by the outcome of
the election?

41:53.344 --> 41:55.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL BESCHLOSS: They sure
have.

41:55.146 --> 41:59.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, Eisenhower said that,
when Kennedy
defeated his vice president,
Nixon, he felt

41:59.283 --> 42:03.588 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as if he had been hit in the
solar plexus
by a baseball bat.

42:03.621 --> 42:08.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I think, in Barack
Obama's case, if
we hear him tonight not saying
essentially

42:08.826 --> 42:13.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I didn't expect to finish my
presidency giving
this office over to a successor
who wants

42:13.798 --> 42:18.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to destroy much of what I have
tried to do
and who is in many ways almost
the opposite

42:18.803 --> 42:24.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of me, if he just sort of plays
cool, as if
sort of he's unruffled by that,
the best Obama

42:24.976 --> 42:29.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
speeches have been -- and this
is true of
most presidents -- when you
really feel that

42:29.113 --> 42:31.749 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you are hearing his inner
monologue.

42:31.783 --> 42:37.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If this is too rhetorical, if
he's trying
too hard to imitate, let's say,
George Washington's

42:37.221 --> 42:40.024 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
