44:40.878 --> 44:49.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now: using the power and appeal
of the arts
to boost low-performing schools.

44:49.520 --> 44:55.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Arts frequently get cut from
school curricula
due to money and time, but a
pilot program

44:55.192 --> 45:00.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
around the country is trying to
use music,
performance and other arts in
dozens of schools

45:00.965 --> 45:02.934 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to motivate kids.

45:02.967 --> 45:04.435 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has the story.

45:04.468 --> 45:10.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of our weekly series
on Making the
Grade.

45:10.908 --> 45:20.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Making music and
using the
arts to build math and other
skills, that's

45:20.484 --> 45:29.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the theory here at the ReNEW
Cultural Arts
Academy, a public charter school
in New Orleans,

45:29.160 --> 45:33.764 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not long ago, one of the lowest
performing
