math?

45:46.777 --> 45:51.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STUDENT: Because, at my old
school, when we
didn't have any songs for
multiplication,

45:51.315 --> 45:56.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we -- like, half my class used
to get, like,
unsatisfactories, because they
didn't remember

45:56.854 --> 45:58.723 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it for multiplication.

45:58.756 --> 46:02.760 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But now that I'm at this school,
and I'm singing
songs, I can memorize it more.

46:02.793 --> 46:08.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A floor above, an
eighth grade
social studies class uses the
musical "Hamilton"

46:08.566 --> 46:09.934 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to make history come alive.

46:09.967 --> 46:11.736 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Teacher Areonne Howard:

46:11.769 --> 46:15.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AREONNE HOWARD, Teacher, ReNEW
Cultural Arts
Academy: I'm obsessed with
"Hamilton," and

46:15.806 --> 46:25.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
