other schools.

46:44.035 --> 46:48.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMANTHA KING, KID smART: The
general idea
of arts integration is to appeal
to different

46:48.673 --> 46:50.574 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
modalities of children's
learning.

46:50.608 --> 46:58.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So they get to get up and use
perhaps skills
and things that they love or are
drawn to,

46:58.249 --> 47:01.686 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
theater, dance, visual arts,
music.

47:01.719 --> 47:06.323 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we find that, when you put
both things
together, it sticks.

47:06.357 --> 47:09.093 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I mean, they remember things.

47:09.126 --> 47:10.494 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's in their body memory.

47:10.528 --> 47:13.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Kathy Fletcher is
national
director of Turnaround Arts.

47:13.998 --> 47:16.934 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KATHY FLETCHER, National
Director, Turnaround
Arts: The idea is really simple,
and it is

47:16.967 --> 47:23.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
