schools.

47:46.864 --> 47:51.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Seventy percent of its funding
comes from
foundations and the private
sector.

47:51.736 --> 47:53.771 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Turnaround began in eight
schools around the
country.

47:53.804 --> 47:58.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The number recently rose to 68
in 15 states
and the District of Columbia.

47:58.876 --> 48:03.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATHY FLETCHER: In the decades
past, the first
thing to get cut when budgets
are going are

48:03.647 --> 48:05.516 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the arts.

48:05.549 --> 48:11.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think a lot of people
thought that families
would get their own art lessons
and dance

48:11.222 --> 48:12.957 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
classes.

48:12.990 --> 48:15.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there's about six million
kids in this
country who are in public
schools, charter

48:16.026 --> 48:19.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
