opportunities,
so they don't get any arts in
school.

48:20.030 --> 48:25.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to have something that
positive and that
joyful to kick-start literacy
and a lot of

48:25.803 --> 48:31.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the other core content subjects,
it just seems
like a smart way to teach.

48:31.942 --> 48:38.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: That strikes a
personal chord
in the Turnaround artists,
accomplished professionals

48:38.816 --> 48:42.253 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who volunteer their time to work
with students
and teachers.

48:42.286 --> 48:49.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At ReNEW Dolores T. Aaron
Academy, we watched
actress Alfre Woodard, singer
Graham Nash

48:49.593 --> 48:52.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and our own David Brooks, The
New York Times
columnist, in action.

48:52.630 --> 48:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALFRE WOODARD, Actress: So, let
me hear the
sound it makes.

48:56.333 --> 48:57.902 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Ah.

48:57.935 --> 48:59.503 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Never hold sound in.

48:59.537 --> 49:01.372 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
STUDENT: I have been watching
the news.

49:01.405 --> 49:03.040 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: And just remember
to take your
time.

49:03.073 --> 49:04.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're going to want to, like,
rush through
because you will be a little
nervous.

49:04.975 --> 49:11.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But if you can stop and breathe,
it will seem
long to you, but it will seem
great to everybody

49:11.248 --> 49:12.616 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
else.

49:12.650 --> 49:14.218 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GRAHAM NASH, Musician: Can you
feel the vibrations
in the guitar?

49:14.251 --> 49:16.187 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
